To associate a file extension with  on Windows:

go to the Start menu and click Control
            Panel;

go to Default Programs;

click Associate a file type or protocol with a program;

click the file extension you want to associate with , then click
            Change program;

in the Open With dialog click Browse and
          navigate to .

To associate a file extension with  on Mac:

In Finder, right click a file and from the contextual menu select
            Get Info;

In the Open With subsection, select Other
          from the application combo and browse to ;

With  selected, click Change All.
